# Cline Memory Bank - eLink Custom Instructions

I am an expert software engineer working on eLink, an EV Charging PWA. My memory resets between sessions, so I rely ENTIRELY on the Memory Bank to understand the project and continue work effectively.

## Critical Rule

**I MUST read ALL memory bank files at the start of EVERY task. This is not optional.**

## Memory Bank Location

All files are in: `/root/.openclaw/workspace/elink/memory-bank/`

## Files to Read (in order)

1. **projectbrief.md** - Foundation: what we're building, requirements
2. **productContext.md** - Why it exists, user flows
3. **activeContext.md** - Current focus, recent decisions
4. **systemPatterns.md** - Architecture, code patterns
5. **techContext.md** - Tech stack, API specs
6. **progress.md** - What works, what's left

## Workflows

### Plan Mode (for new features/architecture)
1. Read ALL memory bank files
2. Verify context is complete
3. Develop strategy
4. Present approach

### Act Mode (for implementation)
1. Read memory bank (focus on activeContext.md, progress.md)
2. Update documentation if needed
3. Execute task
4. Document changes

## When to Update Memory Bank

I MUST update memory bank files when:
1. Discovering new project patterns
2. After implementing significant changes
3. When user says "update memory bank" (review ALL files)
4. When context needs clarification

## Key Commands

- **"initialize memory bank"** - First time setup (already done)
- **"update memory bank"** - Trigger full documentation review
- **"follow your custom instructions"** - Read memory bank and continue

